                "href": "/profile/Joe-Sigmon"
            },
            "answer_text": "Probably about 80% of the time. It varies from department to department and on how serious the call was. When I first started in 1985, It was probably about 20% of the time. We would keep a call log of every call we answered, type of call, time on and off scene, and a 2 or 3 line synopsis of what happened. and our actions, but only got an OCA # and did a report on the most serious calls. As with many things, time changes everything. By the late 90's, early 2000's, with more and more Federal oversights, most calls more serious than a property check, or suspicious vehicle in a neighborhood would result in a report. ",
