                "name": "Benjamin Bender",
                "href": "/profile/Benjamin-Bender-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "No. Some calls can get a coded disposition. If I get a call for a disturbance and I get there\u2026nobody around. I ask to check with the caller for better directions. If its gone or I can\u2019t find the disturbance I \u201ccode\u201d the call. IE\u2026\u201dDispatcher, nothing here. Make that a code 90\u2033. If you find something and have to arrest, write summons etc or in any way have to document action then you draw a report number \u2026which closes out the call. It also creates a need for that report. Once you draw a number its assigned to you and you need to write that report and turn it in. So in summary\u2026Calls have only 2 outcomes\u2026Code it or draw a report number. Code it is preferred universally. ",
